Research suggests that older fathers may contribute to an increased risk of schizophrenia in their children.
The risk is small but rises with paternal age, potentially leading to 720 additional cases in 2002.
Concern over cannabis use in France has prompted a 10-million euro campaign to highlight its harmful effects.
Australian researchers have linked thinning grey matter in the brain to impaired thought processes in schizophrenia.
Additionally, a genetic region promoting fertility and longevity in Europeans has been discovered.
Efforts are underway to create a detailed model of the human brain's neocortex, aiming to enhance understanding of brain function.
